---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <header class="hero">
    <p class="kicker">WaveNav Labs</p>
    <h1>WAP Emulator Stack For Deterministic Engine Work</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      A pre-alpha layered emulator stack focused on WML deck/card fidelity, strict layer boundaries,
      and reproducible behavior across parser, runtime, and host integration.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a class="button" href="./simulator/">Open Simulator</a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="content">
    <section class="panel">
      <h2>Stack Layers</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Gateway:</strong> kannel environment + protocol behavior</li>
        <li><strong>Transport:</strong> WBXML and constrained transport APIs</li>
        <li><strong>Engine:</strong> Rust/WASM WML parser, runtime, layout, navigation</li>
        <li><strong>Desktop Host:</strong> simulator harness and integration adapters</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="panel">
      <h2>Current Focus</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Deterministic deck/card navigation semantics</li>
        <li>Stable wasm contract for host integration</li>
        <li>Repeatable fixture-driven engine behavior</li>
        <li>Manual and scripted validation through simulator timelines</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="panel">
      <h2>Simulator</h2>
      <p>
        The simulator includes curated fixtures, metadata-driven acceptance checklists,
        runtime state snapshots, and per-example event tracking with export.
      </p>
      <p><a class="inline-link" href="./simulator/">Launch /simulator</a></p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer class="footer">
    <p>WaveNav Labs · Pre-alpha WAP/WML engine development</p>
  </footer>
</Layout>
